race.comment: VALLEY PRINCE (2) was plainer last time as favourite in stronger, but was tracking well prior. Maps well and despite the weight rise and deserves another chance. SHEER REWARD (5) settled last three weeks ago over 1200m and had too much to do. He impressed the one prior winning this grade over 1400m. Keeps the handy 3kg claim and the longer sprint should be an issue. SILENTDEEL (4) has been plainer his last two getting back. He'd be in the finish putting his best foot forward. INCIVILITY (6) has also been plainer his last two but the form prior reads well. Has the rail and a handy 2kg claim today and keep safe. TITANIUM PRINCE (3) needs to lift to win but won't be far away.
